HEADWORD: Lemaireocereus
<hw>Lemaireocereus</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A genus of tropical American
cacti, usually tall and branching with stout spines and funnel-shaped
flowers and globular or ovoid often edible fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Lemaireocereus</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
